text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia nyssophylla is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt and Goldfields-Esperance regions of Western Australia.The intricate prickly shrub typically grows to a height of 0.5 to 3 metres (2 to 10 ft). It blooms from July to October and produces yellow flowers.
